    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="876"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.711</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-10">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>15. Following telegram from Legation, Athens.</p>
                <p>Messenger from Consul <persName corresp="#p_HG1">Horton</persName>, Smyrna, asks
                    me to telegraph Department that United States official mail under seal refused
                    by Turkish post office who demand that it be posted open for their
                    inspection.</p>
                <p>Please enter proper protest to Turkish authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
